sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Clough Global Opportunities Fund Section 19(a) Notice
feed.summary: The Clough Global Opportunities Fund (GLO) announced a monthly distribution of $0.0537 per share to shareholders of record as of February 18, 2026, paid on February 27, 2026. The notice highlights that 100% of both the current and fiscal year-to-date cumulative distributions are estimated to be a return of capital. The fund also provided estimated distribution sources and stressed that these figures are for informational purposes, with actual tax reporting to be provided via Form 1099-DIV.

feed.title: Baron Durable Advantage Fund Adjusts Holdings, Adds Quanta Services (PWR)
feed.summary: The Baron Durable Advantage Fund achieved a 2.6% return in Q4 2025, closely matching the S&P 500 Index's 2.7% gain. The fund initiated a new position in Quanta Services (PWR) and increased stakes in Danaher (DHR), while reducing holdings in Broadcom (AVGO), Mastercard (MA), and Intuit (INTU). Quanta Services, a leading provider of specialty contracting services, demonstrated robust financial health with significant revenue growth but its valuation metrics suggest it is trading at elevated levels compared to historical norms.

feed.title: Essex Property Trust (ESS) Downgraded to Market Perform by Raymond James
feed.summary: Raymond James has downgraded Essex Property Trust (ESS) from an 'Outperform' to a 'Market Perform' rating, with analyst Buck Horne responsible for the change. The downgrade occurred on February 27, 2026, and no new price target was announced. This follows other recent analyst adjustments for ESS, including a reiterated 'Overweight' from Cantor Fitzgerald at $300, and downgrades/price target reductions from BMO Capital and Jefferies.

feed.title: Your DTE bill is going up. Utility already has another hike in plans
feed.summary: DTE Energy is set to seek another electric rate increase in April, just days after state regulators approved a $242.4 million hike that will impact customer bills starting March 5. This new request, if approved, would likely not take effect until 2027 due to the typical year-long regulatory process. The utility notified the Michigan Public Service Commission of its intentions on February 24.

feed.title: Autonomous Research Adjusts T. Rowe Price Group PT to $83 From $87, Maintains Underperform Rating
feed.summary: Autonomous Research has revised its price target for T. Rowe Price Group (TROW) to $83, down from $87, while maintaining an "Underperform" rating on the stock. This adjustment reflects a moderated outlook on the investment management company's future performance. The article also touches upon a recent increase in T. Rowe Price's stake in Brazil's Vivara.

feed.title: After moving headquarters out of town, Charles Schwab has a new home in San Francisco
feed.summary: Charles Schwab is relocating its San Francisco offices to 425 Market St., ending its nearly two-decade stay at 211 Main St., which previously served as its headquarters. This move comes after the company shifted its headquarters out of San Francisco. The specific details of the lease and timeline were not immediately available beyond the confirmation of the relocation from a company spokesperson.

feed.title: Sleep Tech Demand Fuels ResMed
feed.summary: ResMed is transitioning from a medical device manufacturer to a digital health platform, driven by increasing demand for sleep apnea therapy, margin expansion, and recurring software revenue. While pharmaceutical treatments for obesity and sleep apnea pose a long-term competitive threat, the company's integrated software ecosystem and strong financial performance indicate continued growth. Its latest Q2 Fiscal Year 2026 results show approximately $1.4 billion in revenue, an 11% year-over-year increase, with significant profit growth attributed to manufacturing efficiencies and a favorable product mix.

feed.title: [Form 4] FLOWERS FOODS INC Insider Trading Activity
feed.summary: David M. Roach, Chief DSD Operations Officer at Flowers Foods Inc., reported insider trading activity. On February 25, 2026, he acquired 10,672 shares through the vesting of contingent performance share units and disposed of 4,343 shares at $9.65 each to cover tax obligations. Following these transactions, Mr. Roach directly holds 157,865 shares and indirectly holds an additional 20,341.39 shares via a 401(k) plan.

feed.title: Royal Bank Of Canada Forecasts Strong Price Appreciation for Targa Resources (NYSE:TRGP) Stock
feed.summary: Royal Bank of Canada has raised its price target for Targa Resources (NYSE:TRGP) to $260 from $218, maintaining an "outperform" rating and implying a 10.49% upside. This follows Targa's recent quarterly earnings report where it surpassed EPS estimates but slightly missed revenue projections. Insiders also sold a substantial amount of shares, totaling approximately $7.6 million.

feed.title: Generac settles $200M lawsuit over 2023 generator explosion
feed.summary: Generac Power Systems has agreed to a $206 million settlement in a lawsuit stemming from a 2023 portable generator explosion that injured six workers in Pennsylvania. The settlement, split between the company and its insurer, allows Generac to resolve all claims while denying any wrongdoing. The incident was linked to a GP15000E portable generator, a model recalled in September 2023 due to a fuel tank issue posing fire and burn hazards.

feed.title: Gilead Sciences Inc Stock Moved Up by 3.72% on Feb 27: What Investors Need To Know
feed.summary: Gilead Sciences Inc.'s stock rose 3.72% on February 27, driven by its $7.8 billion acquisition of Arcellx Inc. to enhance its oncology portfolio, strong Q4 2025 financial results with a 5% increase in product sales, and FDA approval for expanded use of its Yescarta lymphoma treatment. The company also presented positive data from its HIV treatment pipeline, contributing to an optimistic analyst sentiment despite some valuation concerns.

feed.title: Masco (MAS) CFO uses 6,565 shares to cover equity award taxes
feed.summary: Masco Corporation's VP, CFO & Treasurer, Richard J. Westenberg, reported a tax-related disposition of 6,565 shares of common stock. These shares, valued at $71.86 each, were transferred to cover tax liabilities associated with an equity award. Following this transaction, Westenberg directly holds 40,576 shares of Masco common stock.

feed.title: Masco (NYSE: MAS) VP disposes shares to cover tax obligations
feed.summary: Richard Allan Marshall, Vice President at Masco Corporation, reported a tax-related disposition of 515 shares of Masco common stock on February 25, 2026, at a price of $71.86 per share. This transaction was executed to satisfy tax liabilities. Following this disposition, Marshall directly owns 17,496 Masco shares.

feed.title: Masco (MAS) VP and CAO sells shares, disposes stock for taxes
feed.summary: Heath M. Eisman, VP, Controller, and CAO of Masco Corporation (MAS), reported two recent stock transactions. He sold 747 shares on the open market at $71.915 each and disposed of 379 shares at $71.860 each to cover tax obligations. Following these transactions, Eisman directly holds 12,510 Masco common shares.

feed.title: Flowers Foods (FLO) legal chief awarded shares and withholds stock for taxes
feed.summary: Flowers Foods' Chief Legal Counsel, Stephanie B. Tillman, was granted 18,704 shares of common stock at no cost. To cover tax obligations related to this award, 8,319 shares were withheld at a price of $9.65 per share. Following these transactions, Tillman directly holds 110,098 common shares, with additional indirect holdings in a 401(k) and children's accounts.

feed.title: Altria (MO) VP Katie Patterson receives 1,432-share equity award
feed.summary: Altria Group's Vice President and Controller, Katie F. Patterson, was granted 1,432 shares of common stock on February 25, 2026, as an equity award at no cash cost. Following this transaction, her direct holdings increased to 18,357 shares, which include 12,875 restricted stock units. Additionally, her spouse indirectly holds 266 shares, as detailed in the SEC Form 4 filing.

feed.title: Altria (MO) SVP Heather Newman receives 11,973-share equity grant, totals 158,391
feed.summary: Altria Group's Senior Vice President, Heather A. Newman, was granted 11,973 shares of common stock on February 25, 2026, as part of the company's equity compensation plans. This grant increased her directly held position to 158,391 shares, which includes 87,479 restricted stock units, and she also indirectly holds 5,499 shares through a deferred profit-sharing plan. The transaction was reported in an SEC Form 4 filing, indicating an acquisition rather than a purchase or sale.

feed.title: SBA COMMUNICATIONS CORP SEC 10-K Report
feed.summary: SBA Communications Corp (SBAC) released its 2025 10-K report, showcasing significant financial growth with total revenue up 5.5% and net income increasing by 5.7%. The report detailed the company's strong performance in site leasing, strategic acquisitions, and expansion in international markets, while also outlining challenges posed by market competition, reliance on major customers, and operational risks. SBAC plans further growth through asset portfolio expansion, stock repurchases, and dividend payouts, exploring new technologies to diversify revenue.

feed.title: Tapestry Stock: A Deep Dive Into Analyst Perspectives (15 Ratings)
feed.summary: Over the past three months, 15 analysts have evaluated Tapestry (NYSE: TPR), resulting in a mix of bullish and bearish sentiments. The average 12-month price target for Tapestry has increased by 9.01% to $152.4, with a high estimate of $180.00 and a low of $123.00. The company shows strong financial health with high market capitalization, a positive revenue trend, and excellent net margin, ROE, and ROA, though it has a higher debt-to-equity ratio compared to its industry peers.

feed.title: Procter & Gamble remains among Fortune’s Most Admired Companies worldwide
feed.summary: Procter & Gamble has once again been recognized as one of Fortune's Most Admired Companies, securing the 19th position globally and maintaining its All-Star status in the 2026 ranking. This achievement highlights the company's consistent performance in meaningful innovation, operational excellence, and responsible leadership. P&G's ability to serve over 5 billion consumers worldwide daily is attributed to its strong organizational focus on efficiency, innovation, and talent development, reinforced by its global workforce.

feed.title: Sysco Corporation (NYSE:SYY) Plans $0.54 Quarterly Dividend
feed.summary: Sysco Corporation (NYSE:SYY) has declared a quarterly dividend of $0.54 per share, payable on April 24th to shareholders of record on April 2nd. This marks 57 consecutive years of dividend increases, with a sustainable payout ratio of 46.4%. Analysts maintain a "Moderate Buy" rating for SYY, projecting strong future earnings coverage for the dividend.

feed.title: Judge Dismisses Disability Discrimination Suit Against Apple
feed.summary: A judge dismissed a lawsuit against Apple Inc. filed by Robert Bailey, who alleged disability discrimination after being fired in 2023 at age 79. Bailey claimed his termination stemmed from requests for health accommodations and medical leave, though Apple stated he was fired for violating policy by assisting a customer with an Apple ID password recovery. The judge ruled that Apple provided a legitimate business reason for the termination and found no evidence that the policy violation was an excuse to fire Bailey due to his health.

feed.title: Is It Too Late To Consider Stryker (SYK) After Recent Share Price Strength?
feed.summary: Stryker (SYK) has seen recent share price strength, but its current valuation suggests it might be slightly overvalued. A Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) analysis places its fair value near its current trading price, while its P/E ratio is higher than industry averages. The article presents bull and bear case narratives for Stryker, highlighting potential future growth drivers and risks.

feed.title: GLOBAL PARTNERS LP SEC 10-K Report
feed.summary: Global Partners LP has released its 2025 10-K report, detailing robust financial performance with $18,561 million in total sales, a gross profit of $1,062 million, but a decrease in net income and EBITDA. The company expanded its marine fuel supply into the Gulf Coast and made strategic real estate investments, while facing market, operational, regulatory, and environmental risks.

feed.title: Global Partners’ net income in fourth-quarter 2025 grows compared with 2024
feed.summary: Global Partners announced an increase in net income for the fourth quarter of 2025, reaching $25.1 million compared to $23.9 million in the same period of 2024. Despite this quarterly growth, the company's full-year 2025 net income decreased to $98 million from $110.3 million in 2024. The Gasoline Distribution and Station Operations segment performed strongly, helping to offset less favorable conditions in the wholesale segment, as reported by CEO Eric Slifka.

feed.title: New Fairfield community rings 21-acre lake with homes from mid-$600Ks
feed.summary: Century Communities (NYSE: CCS) is opening a new neighborhood called Sunflower at One Lake in Fairfield, CA, where homes will start from the mid-$600,000s. The community features two-story homes with 3–5 bedrooms and access to a 21-acre recreational lake, parks, trails, and a clubhouse. A grand opening event will be held on Saturday, February 28, 2026, offering tours of furnished model homes and limited-time savings.

feed.title: Franklin Street Properties: $320 Million Secured Credit Facility Refinances Debt And Advances Strategic Review
feed.summary: Franklin Street Properties has closed a $320 million secured credit facility with TPG Credit, refinancing all outstanding indebtedness and providing financial flexibility. The company used an initial drawdown of $258.5 million to repay $248.9 million in debt and has the option for additional delayed draw term loans for property improvements. This refinancing addresses near-term debt maturities and allows FSP to continue evaluating strategic alternatives to maximize shareholder value.

feed.title: Washington’s FS Bancorp boosts Portland presence
feed.summary: FS Bancorp is set to acquire Oregon-based Pacific West in a $34.6 million merger, expected to close in Q3. This deal will expand 1st Security Bank of Washington's presence in the Portland metropolitan area by adding Pacific West's four branches. The combined entity will boast 31 locations, $3.6 billion in assets, $3 billion in deposits, and $3 billion in loans, enhancing FS Bancorp's footprint in the Pacific Northwest.

feed.title: Assessing West Pharmaceutical Services (WST) Valuation As Mixed Returns Contrast With Diverging Fair Value Estimates
feed.summary: West Pharmaceutical Services (WST) is experiencing mixed stock returns, prompting a re-evaluation of its valuation. While one narrative suggests the company is 26.4% undervalued with a fair value of $338.57 due to growth in drug delivery systems and GLP-1s, a Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model indicates it is overvalued at $102.89 against a current price of $249.02. Investors are encouraged to consider these diverging perspectives and individual risk tolerance.

feed.title: Edgewell Personal Care to Webcast Fireside Chat at the 47th Annual Raymond James Institutional Investors Conference
feed.summary: Edgewell Personal Care Company announced it will participate in a fireside chat at the 47th Annual Raymond James Institutional Investors Conference on March 4, 2026. President and CEO Rod Little and CFO Francesca Weissman will present. A live webcast and replay of the event will be available on the company's investor relations website.

feed.title: Humana Statement on our Contract with Moffitt Health System
feed.summary: Humana announced that Moffitt Health System and Moffitt Cancer Center in Florida will be out-of-network for Humana Medicare Advantage members starting July 1, 2026. The company is committed to helping members transition to other in-network providers, particularly those undergoing treatment, and has established a customer support line for assistance. Emergency services will remain covered at the in-network benefit level regardless of hospital network participation.

feed.title: Host Hotels And Resorts HST Q4 FFO Strength Tests Bearish Earnings Decline Narrative
feed.summary: Host Hotels & Resorts (HST) reported strong Q4 FY 2025 results with US$1.6 billion in revenue and US$340 million in FFO, exceeding last year's figures. Despite this performance, analysts are forecasting declining EPS over the next three years and a one-off gain of US$167 million complicates the earnings trend, leading to mixed sentiment among investors regarding the company's future growth and valuation.

feed.title: Globe Life (NYSE: GL) director Derek Kan reports zero share ownership
feed.summary: Globe Life (NYSE: GL) director Derek T. Kan filed a Form 3, an initial statement of beneficial ownership, reporting zero shares of Globe Life common stock. This filing indicates he holds no direct or indirect beneficial ownership in the company following the reported holdings. The document details his role as a director and confirms no stock transactions are reflected in this report.

feed.title: Globe Life (NYSE: GL) director Sandra Phillips reports zero share ownership
feed.summary: Globe Life (NYSE: GL) director Sandra L. Phillips has filed an initial Form 3, reporting zero

feed.title: Chains like Sweetgreen and Chipotle are finally realizing they need to look beyond the “slop bowl”
feed.summary: Restaurant chains Sweetgreen, Chipotle, and Cava, which built their businesses on "bowl-based" food, are now seeking to diversify their offerings due to "bowl fatigue" and high menu prices. Sweetgreen is introducing wraps to combat declining sales, while Chipotle is focusing on protein-oriented options. Cava is also expanding its menu with new dishes like pomegranate-glazed salmon, although its CEO defends the continued popularity of bowls.

feed.title: Sameer Gaur, pres. at Wabtec, sells $302k in stock
feed.summary: Sameer Gaur, President, Global Freight Services at Westinghouse Air Brake Technologies (WAB), sold 1,150 shares of company stock for approximately $302,015. This transaction occurred as WAB shares traded near their 52-week high, with the company recently reporting strong Q4 2025 financial results. Despite the positive earnings, InvestingPro analysis suggests WAB is currently overvalued.

feed.title: Assessing Raymond James Financial (RJF) Valuation After Recent Cooling In Short Term Share Momentum
feed.summary: Raymond James Financial (RJF) has experienced mixed share performance recently, with a short-term decline despite stronger longer-term returns, prompting a valuation assessment. The company appears undervalued, with an intrinsic discount of approximately 35% compared to its stock price, and a fair value estimated at $184.83. This undervaluation is supported by strategic investments in AI, robust loan growth in its banking segment, and high credit quality, though market uncertainties and slower asset growth pose risks.

feed.title: Is Motorola Solutions (MSI) Pricing In Too Much After Strong Multi‑Year Share Gains?
feed.summary: Motorola Solutions (MSI) has seen significant share gains, closing at US$471.95, and its valuation is being assessed. Both a Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) analysis and a Price-to-Earnings (P/E) ratio comparison suggest the stock may be overvalued. The DCF model estimates an intrinsic value of $379.88 per share, indicating the current price is about 24.2% higher, while its current P/E of 36.30x is above its calculated Fair Ratio of 26.30x.

feed.title: A Look At First American Financial (FAF) Valuation After Strong Q4 Growth And Analyst Outlook Upgrades
feed.summary: First American Financial (FAF) has shown strong Q4 growth, with adjusted revenue and EPS increasing significantly, driven by commercial revenue growth and improved operating leverage. The company's shares are up year-to-date, trading at $68.29 against an average analyst target of $79.40. While a narrative fair value suggests a 13.3% undervaluation at $78.80, its P/E ratio is slightly above peers but below the US insurance industry average, presenting a mixed signal for investors.

feed.title: Host Hotels And Resorts HST Q4 FFO Strength Tests Bearish Earnings Decline Narrative
feed.summary: Host Hotels & Resorts (HST) reported Q4 2025 revenues of US$1.6 billion and FFO of US$340 million, with basic EPS rising from US$0.15 to US$0.20. Despite this strength and a 9.8% earnings increase year-over-year, analysts forecast a 7.8% decline in EPS over the next three years. The article discusses how these strong recent results challenge the bearish outlook, though a one-off US$167 million gain complicates the underlying earnings trend.

feed.title: Assessing West Pharmaceutical Services (WST) Valuation As Mixed Returns Contrast With Diverging Fair Value Estimates
feed.summary: West Pharmaceutical Services (WST) has shown mixed stock returns recently, prompting a re-evaluation of its valuation. While an analyst narrative suggests the stock is 26.4% undervalued with a fair value of $338.57 due to growth in GLP-1s and high-margin components, a discounted cash flow (DCF) model indicates it is overvalued at $102.89. Investors are encouraged to consider these diverging fair value estimates and personal risk tolerance when assessing the stock.

feed.title: Cintas Awards Highlight Management Strength While Valuation And Debt Draw Scrutiny
feed.summary: Cintas (NasdaqGS:CTAS) has recently been recognized as one of America's best-managed companies and a top large employer for 2026, highlighting its corporate governance and workforce practices. While these awards indicate strong management, the article notes that Cintas's shares trade above Simply Wall St's estimated fair value and pose a risk due to a high level of debt. Investors are advised to consider these factors, alongside the company's P/E ratio, when evaluating Cintas.

feed.title: Five Below Coming To The Marketplace At Warsaw Fall 2026
feed.summary: Five Below is set to open a new location at the Marketplace in Warsaw this fall, occupying a nearly 10,000-square-foot space between Bealls and Ollie's Outlet. This opening, along with a future Hobby Lobby, will significantly increase the shopping center's occupancy from 14% to almost 90%, according to John Murphy of Sullivan Wickley. The city of Warsaw and Mayor Jeff Grose were thanked for their support in revitalizing the Marketplace.

feed.title: Judge Dismisses Man’s Disability Discrimination Suit Against Apple
feed.summary: A Los Angeles Superior Court judge has dismissed a lawsuit filed by Robert Bailey against Apple Inc. Bailey alleged disability discrimination, retaliation, and failure to accommodate after being terminated at age 79. The judge ruled that Apple provided a legitimate business reason for the termination, stating Bailey violated policy by initiating an account recovery request on a customer's behalf, and there was no evidence of discrimination.

feed.title: Lululemon founder says board's response to his suggestions 'weak and insufficient'
feed.summary: Lululemon founder Chip Wilson is escalating his pressure on the company's board, stating their response to his suggestions for board changes and a brand product committee was "weak and insufficient." Lululemon, however, claims they have engaged in good faith and that Wilson has prevented them from interviewing his director nominees. Wilson, a significant shareholder, is pushing for changes due to the company's declining stock value, CEO succession issues, and struggles with recruiting new board members.

feed.title: Next Generation Handheld Raman Analyzer
feed.summary: Thermo Fisher Scientific has introduced the new TruScan G3 Handheld Raman Analyzer, designed for portable raw material identification in the pharmaceutical and biotechnology industries. This device allows for quick, non-destructive identity testing of materials, even through sealed packaging, thereby reducing the need for traditional lab testing. Key features include a built-in touchscreen, improved sensor performance, updated compound libraries, an immersion probe for in situ testing, and enhanced connectivity for data compliance.

feed.title: Quest Diagnostics stock reaches all-time high at 213.21 USD
feed.summary: Quest Diagnostics (DGX) stock has reached a new all-time high of $213.35, demonstrating a 25.34% return over the last year and a 22.21% year-to-date performance. Despite this achievement, InvestingPro analysis suggests the stock may be overvalued. Recent positive developments include exceeding Q4 2025 earnings and revenue expectations, and the appointment of Benjamin Beauvalot as Senior Vice President, Chief Strategy and M&A Officer.

feed.title: DTE Energy to seek another electric rate increase after $242 million hike
feed.summary: DTE Energy plans to seek another electricity rate increase in Michigan, just days after the Michigan Public Service Commission approved a $242 million hike. Attorney General Dana Nessel criticized the system for allowing utilities to request frequent increases, while DTE argues that investments improve reliability and keep bills relatively low. A proposed bill aims to extend the period between rate increase applications to three years, but utilities like Consumers Energy contend that annual adjustments help manage costs more effectively.

feed.title: What brewery workers are up against: The international operations of Molson Coors and Anheuser-Busch
feed.summary: The article discusses the brewing labor struggles against Molson Coors and Anheuser-Busch, highlighting their global operations, automation efforts, and financial strategies. It argues that workers need an international, rank-and-file led strategy to counter these powerful multinational corporations, emphasizing the commonality of struggles across industries like logistics and auto manufacturing.

feed.title: Zacks Industry Outlook Highlights Costco Wholesale, Ross Stores, Target and Dollar General
feed.summary: The Retail – Discount Stores industry continues to thrive by focusing on value and efficiency, attracting consumers amidst inflationary pressures. Key trends include resilient consumer spending, a sustained search for bargains, enhanced omnichannel capabilities, and disciplined margin management. Zacks Investment Research highlights Costco Wholesale Corp., Ross Stores, Inc., Target Corp., and Dollar General Corp. as leading companies in this sector, each showing strategic strengths in their market positions and financial outlooks.
